rComments: The teaching styles of this professor are okay in my opinion. Did not help at all when visited during office hours, and she is not understanding at all.
Very nice and kind prof. I like the way she takes up questions in class. Very easily understood and an easy A for chem lovers

She was so sweet and she cared so much about the students, it sucks she is retiring :( she was a little boring sometimes but she was very explicit about what would be on the exam and stuff. The midterm was a challenging but not unfair. Her section on the exam was very simple. Unfortunately the same cannot be said for the other parts of the exam :(
Her midterms are sooo straight forward jus memories the textbook and do all recommended questions and its an easy 80

Great professor! She is clear is what she is going to include in her exams, you would do great if you do her practice questions. Very helpful if you are stuck in a question, I'm getting her again for CHMA11 I'm sure I will love this class as equally as I loved part 1 of chemistry!

She was a great professor! She was very helpful and did a lot to help students understand the concepts of Introductory Chemistry.(Used many examples and practice questions in her lectures). Her exams were easy to fair and she was always there for assistance.
She's SO boring. My gosh. Her accent is sometimes hard to listen past. I can't count the number of times I fell asleep..
She isn't really a good prof. I didn't enjoyed at her lectures
SHE IS THE BEST CHEM UNDERGRAD PROF. PERIOD! SHE GIVES INCLASS DISCUSSED QUESTIONS ON THE MIDTERM, WHAT MORE YOU WANT? EASY TO PULL A 80+ GRADE.

I really enjoyed her lectures! She was very enthusiastic and was extremely clear when explaining material. Her exam was also very fair. Appreciate her while she's still there because the second half of this course sucks!
If you can avoid, go! She's not even good to be a prof. She teach bad and the exam is horrible
i can read slides too, can i be a prof?

She is a really amazing prof, she keeps the material relatively easy if you go to lectures and do the practice problems. In office hours she is very helpful and friendly, and explains tough questions really well.
I really did not enjoy her classes. I think she should just retire already. I'm sure she's a nice person tho....:)
Shes an amazing prof. teaches the material very well i found it very usefull going to the lectures. Her exams are not hard at all. Just make sure you do the practice questions she assigns.

First of all, do the assigned questions you'll be fine on exams and such. If you need help, don't go to her she's not very approachable. She has piercing eagle eyes and going to her office hours and trying to explain your problem is torture, with her staring at you. I say go to the chem aid centre.
easy exams to get 90s. but extremely useless lectures since she reads from the slides. better off learning at home. as long as she keeps her papers simlpe shes nice at least
Great professor truly cares about her students and makes chemistry learnable.

Horrible prof. I have never disliked a course as much as chemistry when she taught it. Not only does she make rediculous amounts of work for you to do (as if we didnt have any more courses), but the TA's for this course are even worse. I have never seen such bad TA's in my university stay as this course offers. Avoid course at all costs.

I don't know why people are complaining, her midterm was a piece of cake, she actually cares about whether the class understands or not. Excellent prof. Do assigned Q's and you're fine. To idiot below me, you were reminded time after time to bring your calculator, her not providing you with a calculator has nothing to do with her ability to teach.
Very bad teacher. Didn't offer calculator during exam. I almost had a panic attack.
Really great prof. Good teaching style, and she so experienced that she is confident and clear about what she is teaching.
she's doing a decent job considiring the material she's working with and she goes at decent pace

Verner is definitely the best and most fair out of all the chem profs at utsc. Students give her a hard time not because of her teaching, but because they simply dont like the material.  Her explanations are clear and much easier than the textbook.  Her exams are one of the fairest I've ever had in my four years here.

not good at all, makes everything seem boring and uninteresting, its a pain to pay attention in class even if you been overdosed with cafeine, only take this course if you plan to study about 6 hours a day for it, otherwize don't expect a decent mark She tends to give few questions on midterms and they are very specific ones! good luck!

lets just say shes an itch.  she's no help at all when you email her and she doesnt even know what shes talking about.  i dont even know why shes the coordinator.  she failed me with 48 percent and when i emailed her twice about help she gave me nothing.  she might seem clear at first but she just makes the material harder than it is.
One of the best profs I have had yet, she is clear what she wants, and she is cares that we get the material.
Fantastic.
Very good course.

course wasn't exactly hard....but it sure felt hard considering how confusing she is. she's strict and doesn't compromise with anyone...even if they're sick with a medical note....or can't make it to a practical cuz of a midterm goin on at the same time.
